00:54:12.423 --> 00:54:13.840 align:middle line:84%
LAWRENCE GUTH:
Yeah, that's right.

00:54:13.840 --> 00:54:18.550 align:middle line:84%
So our set A prime is just
the set of neighbors of one b.

00:54:18.550 --> 00:54:25.568 align:middle line:90%


00:54:25.568 --> 00:54:26.110 align:middle line:90%
That's right.

00:54:26.110 --> 00:54:36.500 align:middle line:90%


00:54:36.500 --> 00:54:40.220 align:middle line:84%
Yeah, maybe at
the end, we'll try

00:54:40.220 --> 00:54:42.320 align:middle line:84%
to look back over the
Balog-Szemeredi-Gowers

00:54:42.320 --> 00:54:44.730 align:middle line:84%
theorem and the
Balog-Szemeredi-Gowers theorem,

00:54:44.730 --> 00:54:47.010 align:middle line:84%
the conclusion is there
exists A prime and B prime,

00:54:47.010 --> 00:54:49.020 align:middle line:84%
so that A prime plus
B prime is small.

00:54:49.020 --> 00:54:52.190 align:middle line:84%
And it's a natural
question, like who

00:54:52.190 --> 00:54:53.490 align:middle line:90%
are A prime plus B prime.

00:54:53.490 --> 00:54:56.210 align:middle line:90%
How do we find them?

00:54:56.210 --> 00:54:57.940 align:middle line:84%
This one I actually
probably should

00:54:57.940 --> 00:54:59.190 align:middle line:90%
have name something different.

00:54:59.190 --> 00:55:01.577 align:middle line:84%
This is not the final
A prime in the end

00:55:01.577 --> 00:55:02.660 align:middle line:90%
of Balog-Szemeredi-Gowers.

00:55:02.660 --> 00:55:04.130 align:middle line:90%
It's a stepping stone.

00:55:04.130 --> 00:55:06.560 align:middle line:84%
But we can keep track
of it along the way

00:55:06.560 --> 00:55:09.060 align:middle line:84%
and see, how do we find
A prime and B prime.

00:55:09.060 --> 00:55:21.325 align:middle line:90%


00:55:21.325 --> 00:55:26.130 align:middle line:84%
So here, most of
the pairs are good.

00:55:26.130 --> 00:55:29.020 align:middle line:84%
And we're going to upgrade
that in a trivial way.

00:55:29.020 --> 00:55:35.340 align:middle line:84%
If you fix a1, we could ask
whether most of the a2 are good.

00:55:35.340 --> 00:55:37.630 align:middle line:84%
And that's not
necessarily going to work.

00:55:37.630 --> 00:55:41.230 align:middle line:84%
There could be a few bad
a1's where many a2's are bad,

00:55:41.230 --> 00:55:45.670 align:middle line:84%
but we just cross them out and
