00:55:45.670 --> 00:55:49.690 align:middle line:84%
and then we could say for every
a1, most of the a2's are good.

00:55:49.690 --> 00:55:50.900 align:middle line:90%
So let me write that down.

00:55:50.900 --> 00:55:56.520 align:middle line:90%


00:55:56.520 --> 00:55:58.920 align:middle line:84%
So I think this is the
best thing that I know how

00:55:58.920 --> 00:56:00.830 align:middle line:90%
to say about paths of length 2.

00:56:00.830 --> 00:56:14.190 align:middle line:90%


00:56:14.190 --> 00:56:19.910 align:middle line:84%
OK, so let me call this lemma
2 for paths of length 2.

00:56:19.910 --> 00:56:24.500 align:middle line:84%
So if x is in A cross
B, the size of X

00:56:24.500 --> 00:56:30.650 align:middle line:84%
is at least K inverse A B
and epsilon is bigger than 0.

00:56:30.650 --> 00:56:38.180 align:middle line:84%
Then there exists A2 in A
so that it's pretty big.

00:56:38.180 --> 00:56:41.670 align:middle line:84%
Not quite as big as
before, but I don't know,

00:56:41.670 --> 00:56:53.840 align:middle line:84%
1/4 K inverse A. And for every a
and a2, a fraction of 1 minus--

00:56:53.840 --> 00:56:57.980 align:middle line:84%
it won't be 1 minus 2 epsilon,
but maybe 1 minus 10 epsilon

00:56:57.980 --> 00:57:02.683 align:middle line:90%
times A2 Of a2.

00:57:02.683 --> 00:57:05.780 align:middle line:90%


00:57:05.780 --> 00:57:09.410 align:middle line:90%
Let me say it this way.

00:57:09.410 --> 00:57:16.740 align:middle line:84%
At most, 10 epsilon times the
size of A2 little a2 and A2,

00:57:16.740 --> 00:57:21.240 align:middle line:84%
there are at most there, so
that the pair little a1, a2, is

00:57:21.240 --> 00:57:22.085 align:middle line:90%
epsilon bad.

00:57:22.085 --> 00:57:28.830 align:middle line:90%


00:57:28.830 --> 00:57:35.570 align:middle line:84%
OK, so proof sketch is just
use the previous lemma.

00:57:35.570 --> 00:57:38.850 align:middle line:90%


00:57:38.850 --> 00:57:43.120 align:middle line:90%
And A2 is a prime.

00:57:43.120 --> 00:57:47.680 align:middle line:84%
Take away the A's that have
too many bad neighbors.

00:57:47.680 --> 00:58:25.450 align:middle line:90%


00:58:25.450 --> 00:58:28.077 align:middle line:84%
Yeah, actually, let me
write this in a better way.

00:58:28.077 --> 00:58:29.660 align:middle line:84%
And then I can draw
the picture of it.

00:58:29.660 --> 00:58:34.840 align:middle line:84%
So for every in A our set,
we can break up the set

00:58:34.840 --> 00:58:38.835 align:middle line:90%
as a bad part with a good part.

00:58:38.835 --> 00:58:41.980 align:middle line:90%


00:58:41.980 --> 00:58:45.420 align:middle line:84%
And what's the feature of each
of these, the bad part is small.

00:58:45.420 --> 00:58:50.380 align:middle line:90%


00:58:50.380 --> 00:58:53.070 align:middle line:84%
And what's good
about the good part?

00:58:53.070 --> 00:59:04.420 align:middle line:90%


00:59:04.420 --> 00:59:06.740 align:middle line:84%
The good part, there are
many paths from a to a2

00:59:06.740 --> 00:59:09.190 align:middle line:90%
in the good part.

00:59:09.190 --> 00:59:10.120 align:middle line:90%
Yeah?

